    <ExplicitInverseRef name="allUpdatesByTransactionIdDict" id="423941e3-8976-4a99-815c-660dd617c9af">
        <updateMode>manual</updateMode>
        <type name="JSSCTChangeByTransactionID"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>When an object create, update or delete record is read from the audit log, or journal, then
a ChangeTrackingObject is created or updated.

This information from the journal may end up being a part of an aborted transaction, and this
information may not be available until another journal file sometime later on.

Therefore, we create these records, but don't make them available until we have the commit transaction
notification.

This collection is added to when a new instance is created or updated, if there is a transaction ID
value on the TransactionAgent. It is subsequently removed if it is blank.</text>
        <Inverse name="JSSCTChangeTrackingObject::myChangeTrackingRoot"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
